  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Production Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Review daily production schedules, ship commits, and job orders to ensure timely execution.</li><li>Follow up closely with production supervisors and line leaders on job progress.</li><li>Resolve bottlenecks, delays, or resource constraints promptly to keep production on schedule.  </li><li>Monitor Work-In-Progress (WIP) and expedite urgent jobs based on customer delivery timelines.</li><li>Highlight and escalate any risk of delay to relevant stakeholders immediately.</li><li>Coordinate priority sequencing with production teams to meet shipment timelines.</li><li>Work with procurement and store teams to ensure material readiness before job start.</li><li>Follow up on pending material or tooling to prevent production stoppages.</li><li>Verify that machines and manpower are allocated appropriately for urgent jobs.</li><li>Update job status trackers, production boards, and ERP/MES system daily.</li><li>Prepare daily production progress reports for management review.</li><li>Ensure timely documentation of job completions, reworks, delays, and changes.</li><li>Perform any other ad hoc duties assigned by the Reporting Manager</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirement</strong></p><ul><li>Strong communication and coordination skills.</li><li>Ability to multitask and manage urgent priorities.</li><li>Good problem‑solving skills and attention to detail.</li><li>Proficient in MS Excel and basic reporting.</li></ul>",
